==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-offside.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
'''offside'''

# (''sports'') in an [[illegal]] [[position]] to [[play]] the [[ball]]
# {{US}} To the side of the road, past the [[curb]] and [[sidewalk]], e.g. an [[offside diner]] (restaurant.)

====Usage notes====
* Precise usage varies between sports; singular [[offside]] is used more in soccer, while the plural form [[offsides]] is used in football.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# (''sports'') an offside [[play]]
# (''British'') the [[side]] of a [[road]] [[vehicle]] [[farthest]] from the [[kerb]]

====Antonyms====
* [[nearside]] (2)

